Utterance.UttText: Dave McKenzie, 72 yrs old, came in under Dr Jorge De Silva with Dementia.
He is a new admission and just arrived few hrs ago.
He's got a long medical history but the latest one are CCF, HPN, DM type 2 on oral hypoglycemics and chronic back pains.
He came in due to increasing confusion.
He is still for bloods and I haven't done them yet and He is for urine MCS.
They are querying UTI for him and they started him on oral abs.
He's from a nursing home and his wife was already informed about him coming to us.
He is resting in bed now and I haven't seen him walk yet.
I think it will be best to refer him to physio and for dietician aswell.
He was refusing the meals that was offered to him. otherwise all his obs are stable.
